---
import LegalLayout from '../../../layouts/LegalLayout.astro'
import { getAppBySlug, LAST_UPDATED, SUPPORT_EMAIL } from '../../../legal-config'

const app = getAppBySlug('gymmate')
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.endsWith('/')
  ? import.meta.env.BASE_URL
  : `${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/`
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Support"
  appName={app.name}
  lastUpdated={LAST_UPDATED}
  description="Support, privacy requests, account deletion, data export, Apple Health, notifications, and account help for GymMate."
>
  <h2>Contact Support</h2>
  <p>
    For help with GymMate, contact <a href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`}>{SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a>.
    Estimated response time is 2-5 business days.
  </p>
  <p>
    GymMate is developed and maintained by Nacho Martínez, operating under the Sizle Digital Product
    Studio brand.
  </p>
  <p>Suggested subject: GymMate Support Request</p>

  <h2>What to Include</h2>
  <p>
    Please include your device model, operating system version, GymMate app version if available, the
    sign-in method you used, and a short description of what happened. Do not email passwords, full
    payment card details, private health records, or recovery codes.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you signed in with Apple and used a private relay email address, please contact support from
    that relay address or include enough information to identify your account.
  </p>

  <h2>Common Support Topics</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Account sign-in, email verification, password reset, or account deletion.</li>
    <li>Training programs, exercises, workout logs, body weight entries, achievements, and stats.</li>
    <li>Offline sync, exported files, data import or export, and local storage issues.</li>
    <li>Apple Health, Apple Watch, Live Activities, widgets, timers, and notifications.</li>
    <li>AI-assisted program parsing, parsing limits, or incorrect parsed programs.</li>
    <li>Analytics consent, privacy requests, or data access requests.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Account Deletion and Data Export</h2>
  <p>
    If you created an account, use the in-app account deletion option where available or contact
    support for assistance. GymMate may ask for verification before processing deletion requests.
  </p>
  <p>
    Deleting the app may remove local app data from your device, but it may not automatically delete
    account-backed records, provider-side records, exported files, or copies stored elsewhere.
  </p>
  <p>
    GymMate provides data export functionality where available. Exported files may include training
    programs, workout logs, body metrics, notes, achievements, notification settings, and other
    account-related records. Keep exported files in a safe location and avoid sharing them with
    people you do not trust.
  </p>

  <h2>Apple Health, Apple Watch, and Notifications</h2>
  <p>
    Apple Health and Apple Watch features require permissions managed by iOS and watchOS. You can
    review or revoke Health permissions in iOS Settings or the Health app. Notification permissions
    can be managed in iOS Settings or browser settings, and notification preferences can be adjusted
    inside GymMate where available.
  </p>

  <h2>Purchases and Subscriptions</h2>
  <p>
    If GymMate offers Apple-billed purchases or subscriptions, they are processed through
    Apple&apos;s App Store. Subscription management, cancellations, and refund requests are handled
    through the user&apos;s Apple ID account and Apple&apos;s App Store settings.
  </p>
  <p>
    To manage or cancel an Apple-billed subscription, open iOS Settings -> Apple Account ->
    Subscriptions. Refund requests for Apple-billed purchases are handled by Apple through <a
      href="https://reportaproblem.apple.com/"
      >reportaproblem.apple.com</a
    >.
  </p>

  <h2>Legal Documents</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href={`${base}apps/${app.slug}/privacy-policy/`}>Privacy Policy</a></li>
    <li><a href={`${base}apps/${app.slug}/terms-of-use/`}>Terms of Use</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Legal Note</h2>
  <p>
    These documents are provided for transparency and app publication workflows. They are not a
    substitute for legal advice from a qualified professional.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
